President Donald Trump has announced his intent to nominate Andrew Bremberg of Virginia as the Representative of the United States of America to the Office of the United Nations and Other International Organizations in Geneva. Bremberg currently serves as Assistant to the President and Director of the Domestic Policy Council. He has a history of public service and has worked for the non-profit MITRE Corporation and the Department of Health and Human Services. In addition, President Trump has announced his intent to appoint Jill L. Nelson of Maryland as a Member of the Federal Salary Council and Justin Shubow of Maryland as a Member of the Commission of Fine Arts.